### Probabilities → Bits

If we know how probable something is, can we calculate how many bits we'd need to represent it?

$$
P(x) = \frac{1}{2^n}
$$

$$
P(x) = 2^{-n}
$$

$$
\log_2 P(x) = -n
$$

$$
-\log_2 P(x) = n
$$


::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}

```{.python .cell-code}
import numpy as np

# 1/8 = 0.125
-np.log2(0.125)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
3.0
```


:::
:::


